text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus longinux is an uncommon Asian species of trees in the beech family. It has only been found in Taiwan.Quercus longinux is a tree. Leaves can be as much as 8 cm long. Acorn is up to 12 mm long, narrower than those of most other species in the subgenus.
